{
  "reference name": "Cross",
  "tutorial header": "CROSS-EXAMINATIONS",
  "tutorial body": "You've started CROSS-EXAMINING a witness. The key to each CROSS-EXAMINATION is to determine which part of the witness's testimony contradicts any of the items in your NOTES. Use the ← → arrows to carefully examine each statement in the witness's testimony. Identify the contradicting statement and PRESENT the item that contradicts it."
}

